OL,6,FMrs Philliskirk said: "The one thing
OL,7,Fwe want is for James to be alive and
OL,8,Fthat cannot happen.
OL,10,F"However, James loved other babies and
OL,11,Fchildren and I think it's very fitting
OL,12,Fthat his legacy will hopefully keep
OL,13,Fother babies and children more safe."
OL,15,FJames contracted chickenpox and
OL,16,Frecovered in April 2022 but a few
OL,17,Fweeks later he became unwell,
OL,18,Fdeveloped a rash and started to make a
OL,19,F"groaning, unsettled and painful
OL,20,Fnoise."
